UID:IfsWT-fKy3dwRHmWYRRCG
SUMMARY:Triple Crown Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260627T134503Z
DTSTART:20260827T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us in honoring Lydia Kavraki (https://news.rice.edu/news/2
	025/national-academy-sciences-elects-lydia-kavraki-member) and Rebecca Ric
	hards-Kortum (https://news.rice.edu/news/2025/richards-kortum-elected-nati
	onal-academy-medicine)\, two scholars whose careers exemplify the highest 
	ideals of research\, innovation\, mentorship and service.  Through groundb
	reaking discoveries\, commitment to students\, and work that has improved 
	lives around the world\, they have advanced their fields and inspired the 
	next generation of researchers\, engineers and scientists. They are also t
	he only two researchers in Texas elected to all three National Academies\,
	 an extraordinary distinction held by fewer than 35 living researchers nat
	ionwide.  The program will feature reflections from university leadership\
	, perspectives from colleagues\, and a conversation with the honorees on t
	he work\, values and experiences that have shaped their remarkable careers
	.RSVP for this special event! (https://engrice.wufoo.com/forms/the-triple-
	crown-of-discovery/)\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/event/432386-triple-crown-
	celebration\n\nFrom Rice University - Open to the Public
URL:https://events.rice.edu/event/432386-triple-crown-celebration
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:Duncan Hall
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
